Beginning in May 1998 two key banks began quoting prices in euros and the Chinese government officially welcomed coming of the euro.
The European Central Bank President predicted that the euro would eventually rival the dollar.
Test printing of euro banknotes began, German minted euro coins and key euro indicators were offered daily on the internet.
By October 1998 Bulgaria had anticipated arrival of the euro by linking its currency to the German mark and Thailand was considering use of the euro for its foreign reserves to stem the volatility of the dollar and yen.
